The &lt;a href="Association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; tournament at the &lt;a href="2001%20Maccabiah%20Games"&gt;2001 Maccabiah Games&lt;/a&gt; was played in Israel between 15 and 22 July.
The men's tournament was won by Argentina, who had beaten Mexico in the finals 2–1.
As well as a senior tournament, tournaments were held for junior boys (won by Israel), masters (won by Argentina) and junior girls (as a demonstration event). 
